mend checking out the research guide for Disability & Human Development .  Recommend an item for the UIC Library collection  Use your knowledge to enhance the UIC Library for all - let us know what books, videos, and other material we should have.                 History of Activism among People with Disabilities      America:  History and Life  America: History and Life provides articles on the history and culture of the United States and Canada, from prehistory to the present.   more...  less...   America: History and Life is a comprehensive bibliography of articles on the history and culture of the United States and Canada from prehistory to the present. AHL offers abstracts and citations for articles appearing in over 2,000 journals published worldwide in history, related humanities, and the social sciences. The database also includes citations to book reviews from approximately 140 major journals of American history and culture, and relevant dissertations from Dissertation Abstracts International.  America: History and Life is a resource for a variety of disciplines, including:  * History * American Studies * Anthropology * Genealogy * Interdisciplinary Studies * Literature/Folklore * Multicultural Studies * Popular Culture * Sociology * Women's Studies/Gender Studies * History of Science, Economics, Business, Education, Music, Art, and Law      E-books in the UIC Library Catalog  Recent e-books about the history of activism in the disabled community.                Books on Disability & Academia            Academic Ableism by Jay T. Dolmage Call Number: LC4818.38 .D66 2017 ISBN: 9780472073719 Publication Date: 2017  Daley Library - Book Stacks       Allies for Inclusion: Disability and Equity in Higher Education by Karen A. Myers,   Jaci Jenkins Lindburg,  and Danielle M. Nied  E-book Publication date 2013            Barriers and Belonging by Michelle Jarman (Editor); Leila Monaghan (Editor); Alison Quaggin Harkin (Editor) Call Number: E-BOOK ISBN: 9781439913871 Publication Date: 2017          College Success for Students with Disabilities by Irene Ingersoll Call Number: LC4818.38 .I64 2016 ISBN: 9781476662886 Publication Date: 2016  Daley Library - Book Stacks           Disability in Higher Education by Nancy J. Evans; Ellen M. Broido; Todd K. McEwing-Herriott; Martha E. Wisbey; Todd K. Herriott; Kirsten R. Brown; Autumn K. Wilke ISBN: 9781118018224 Publication Date: 2017  Daley Library - Book Stacks           Negotiating Disability by Stephanie L. Kerschbaum; Laura T. Eisenman; James M. Jones ISBN: 9780472053704 Publication Date: 2017  Daley Library - Book Stacks                  Streaming videos      Kanopy  Kanopy is an on-demand service providing streaming videos that offers access to a variety of award-winning documentaries, training films, and theatrical releases.        Film Platform  Film platform is a collection of documentary films, that contains number of films pertaining to disabilities, including Life, Animated, Sea of Butterfly, The Punk Syndrome, and Matthew's Laws, which can be browsed by filtering by Topic-> "Disability".                Selected Journals      American journal on intellectual and developmental disabilities     Disability and health journal     Journal of disability policy studies     Review of disability studies                           Last Updated:  Jul 3, 2019 10:03 AM    URL:  https://researchguides.uic.edu/DCCLibraryGuide    Print Page     Staff Login                           Logo for the University of Illinois at Chicago       University  Library          Locations          Richard J. Daley Library    801 S. Morgan   Chicago , IL  60607       Phone  (312) 996-2724              Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago    1750 W. Polk St.   Chicago , IL  60612       Circulation  (312) 996-8966    Reference  (312) 996-9163              Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria    One Illini Drive PO Box 1649   Peoria , IL  61656       Phone  (309) 671-8490              Crawford Library of